sim/aircraft/controls/acf_ailn_tab.description: This is the amount of aileron deflection (as a ratio of max) induced by the aerodynamic effect of static trim tabs.

sim/aircraft/controls/acf_ailn_trim_spee.description: This is the speed of trim time, expressed as a ratio, where 1.0 means it takes 20 seconds to fully move trim from one extreme to the other.  2.0 means trim is twice as fast.

sim/aircraft/controls/acf_elev_def_time.description: Enter 0.0 to be able to deflect the controls as fast as the pilot can move the stick or the art stab system can command a deflection. sim/aircraft/controls/acf_elev_trim_time.description: This is the total time taken for the elevator trim to go from one extreme to the other.

sim/cockpit2/ice/cowling_thermal_anti_ic.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - inlet heat. This switch turns on thermal anti ice of the engine cowling and inlet. This takes hot bleed air from the HP compressor.  Per engine

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_AOA_heat_on.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  AOA sensor heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the AOA sensor. If it freezes up your AOA indicator stops working. AOA sensor failure will also affect the aircraft's artificial stability system if it has one.  Pilot.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_AOA_heat_on_copilot.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  AOA sensor heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the AOA sensor. If it freezes up your AOA indicator stops working. AOA sensor failure will also affect the aircraft's artificial stability system if it has one.  Copilot.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_auto_ignite_on.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - auto-ignition. This switch turns on a continuous ignition source in the engine to automatically relight it if there is a flameout.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_detect_on.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Ice-detection: Turn this switch on to enable ice-detection... if the system detects ice, it will light up the ICE annunciator.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_inlet_heat_on.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - inlet heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the engine air inlet keep ice from choking your engine. Engine 1 only

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_inlet_heat_on_per_e.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - inlet heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the engine air inlet keep ice from choking your engine.  Per engine

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_pitot_heat_on_copil.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Pitot tube heat, co-pilot. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the co-pilot side pitot tube. If it freezes up your airspeed indicator and altimeter stop working. Airspeed and altitude related autopilot functions are also affected.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_pitot_heat_on_pilot.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - pitot tube heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat in the pitot tube. If it freezes up your airspeed indicator and altimeter stop working. Airspeed and altitude related autopilot functions are also affected.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_prop_heat_on.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - prop heat. This switch turns on de-icing of the propeller(s) to keep ice from building up on your prop. Engine 1 only

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_prop_heat_on_per_en.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - prop heat. This switch turns on de-icing of the propeller(s) to keep ice from building up on your prop.  Per engine

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_prop_tks_on_per_eng.description: De-ice switch, 0, 1, or 2.  De-ice - prop TKS. This switch turns on de-icing of the propeller(s) with TKS fluid to keep ice from building up on your prop. 0 = Off, 1 = Norm, 2 = High. Per engine

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_static_heat_on_copi.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Static port heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the static sensor. If it freezes up your altimeter, vvi and airspeed indicator stop working. Copilot.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_static_heat_on_pilo.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  Static port heat. This switch turns on de-icing heat for the static sensor. If it freezes up your altimeter, vvi and airspeed indicator stop working. Pilot.

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_surface_boot_left_o.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - pneumatic. This switch inflates flexible bladders on the wing leading edges to pop off accumulated ice. (Left wing)

sim/cockpit2/ice/ice_surface_boot_on.description: De-ice switch, 0 or 1.  De-ice - pneumatic. This switch inflates flexible bladders on the wing leading edges to pop off accumulated ice. (All wings)

sim/flightmodel2/controls/aileron_trim.description: Aileron trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the aileron trim is deflected enough to move the ailerons through 30% of their travel, then that is an aileron trim of 0.3.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/elevator_trim.description: Elevator trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the elevator trim is deflected enough to move the elevators through 30% of their travel, then that is an elevator trim of 0.3.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/flap1_deploy_r.description: This is the ACTUAL FLAP deployment for flap-set #1, in ratio, where 0.0 is flaps fully retracted, and 1.0 is flaps fully extended.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/flap2_deploy_r.description: This is the ACTUAL FLAP deployment for flap-set #2, in ratio, where 0.0 is flaps fully retracted, and 1.0 is flaps fully extended.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/flap_handle_de.description: This is the ACTUAL FLAP deployment for overall flap system, in ratio, where 0.0 is flaps fully retracted, and 1.0 is flaps fully extended. You should probably use the deployment for flap set 1 or flap set 2 to deflect the surfaces though.  This takes into account that flaps deploy slowly, not instantaneously as the handle is dragged.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/heading_ratio.description: This is how much the flight controls are deflected in heading after any stability augmentation, where -1.0 is full left, and 1.0 is full right.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/incidence_rati.description: Actual incidence, in ratio. 0.0 is no incidence deployment, 1 is max incidence deployment.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/pitch_ratio.description: This is how much the flight controls are deflected in pitch after any stability augmentation, in ratio, where -1.0 is full down, and 1.0 is full up.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/roll_ratio.description: This is how much the flight controls are deflected in roll after any stability augmentation, in ratio, where -1.0 is full left, and 1.0 is full right.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/rotor_trim.description: Rotor trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the rotor trim is deflected enough to move the rotor through 30% of its travel, then that is a rotor trim of 0.3.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/rudder_trim.description: Rudder trim, in part of MAX FLIGHT CONTROL DEFLECTION. So, if the rudder trim is deflected enough to move the rudders through 30% of their travel, then that is an rudder trim of 0.3.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/slat1_deploy_r.description: Slat deployment, where 0.0 is slats fully retracted, 1.0 is slats fully extended. This variable applies to lading-edge flaps as well.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/slat2_deploy_r.description: Slat deployment, where 0.0 is slats fully retracted, 1.0 is slats fully extended. This variable applies to lading-edge flaps as well.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/speedbrake_rat.description: This is how much the speedbrakes surfaces are extended, in ratio, where 0.0 is fully retracted, and 1.0 is fully extended.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/stabilizer_def.description: This is the actual stabilizer deflection with trim for all-moving horizontal stabilizers. This is the deflection you can see visually on airliners. This is in degrees, positive for leading-edge nose up.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/wing_retractio.description: Actual wing-retraction, in ratio. 0.0 is no wing-retraction deployment, 1 is max wing-retraction deployment.

sim/flightmodel2/controls/wingsweep_rati.description: Actual sweep, in ratio. 0.0 is no sweep deployment, 1 is max sweep deployment.
